todos.long_description:
🎯 **Objective:** Categorize tools with tags for selective exposure

📋 **Reference:** https://gofastmcp.com/servers/server#tag-based-filtering

**Tag Categories:**
```python
# Speed-based
@mcp.tool(tags={"quick"})      # < 10 seconds
@mcp.tool(tags={"slow"})       # > 30 seconds

# Workflow-based  
@mcp.tool(tags={"daily"})      # Daily automation
@mcp.tool(tags={"weekly"})     # Weekly maintenance
@mcp.tool(tags={"sprint"})     # Sprint workflows

# Function-based
@mcp.tool(tags={"tasks"})      # Task management
@mcp.tool(tags={"code"})       # Code analysis
@mcp.tool(tags={"docs"})       # Documentation
@mcp.tool(tags={"security"})   # Security scanning
```

**Tool Assignments:**
- quick: server_status, list_tasks_awaiting_clarification
- slow: scan_dependency_security, sprint_automation
- daily: check_documentation_health, run_daily_automation
- weekly: scan_dependency_security, detect_duplicate_tasks

**Usage:**
```python
# Quick tools only for CI
mcp_ci = FastMCP(include_tags={"quick"})

# Exclude slow tools for interactive use
mcp_interactive = FastMCP(exclude_tags={"slow"})
```

🎯 **Objective:** Update config to use FastMCP uv-based format

📋 **Reference:** https://gofastmcp.com/integrations/mcp-json-configuration

**Current format (outdated):**
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "exarp": {
      "command": "/path/to/run_server.sh",
      "args": []
    }
  }
}
```

**Target format (FastMCP standard):**
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "exarp": {
      "command": "uv",
      "args": [
        "run", "--with", "fastmcp",
        "--with", "pydantic", "--with", "networkx",
        "fastmcp", "run",
        "/path/to/server.py"
      ],
      "env": {
        "PROJECT_ROOT": "/path/to/project"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

**Config locations:**
- Cursor: ~/.cursor/mcp.json
- Claude Desktop: ~/.claude/claude_desktop_config.json
- VS Code: .vscode/mcp.json

🎯 **Objective:** Add resource templates for querying data

📋 **Reference:** https://gofastmcp.com/clients/resources

**New resource templates:**
```python
@mcp.resource("exarp://tasks/{status}")
def get_tasks_by_status(status: str) -> list:
    """Get tasks filtered by status."""
    return load_tasks(status=status)

@mcp.resource("exarp://task/{task_id}")
def get_task(task_id: str) -> dict:
    """Get single task by ID."""
    return load_task(task_id)

@mcp.resource("exarp://health/{component}")
def get_health(component: str) -> dict:
    """Get health of specific component."""
    return check_health(component)
```

**Use cases:**
- Query tasks without running full tool
- Access cached analysis results
- Quick data lookups

🎯 **Objective:** Make prompts accept runtime arguments

📋 **Reference:** https://gofastmcp.com/servers/prompts

**Current prompts:** Static strings
**Target:** Accept arguments for customization

**Example:**
```python
@mcp.prompt
def task_review(
    include_stale: bool = True,
    days_threshold: int = 30,
    status_filter: str = None
) -> str:
    """Review tasks with configurable options."""
    prompt = "Review project tasks:\n"
    if include_stale:
        prompt += f"- Include stale tasks (>{days_threshold} days)\n"
    if status_filter:
        prompt += f"- Filter to status: {status_filter}\n"
    return prompt

@mcp.prompt  
def sprint_planning(
    sprint_length: int = 14,
    max_tasks: int = 10
) -> str:
    return f"Plan a {sprint_length}-day sprint with up to {max_tasks} tasks..."
```

🎯 **Objective:** Simple token auth for local development

📋 **Reference:** https://gofastmcp.com/servers/auth/token-verification

**Implementation:**
```python
from fastmcp.server.auth.providers.jwt import StaticTokenVerifier

verifier = StaticTokenVerifier(
    tokens={
        "dev-admin-token": {
            "client_id": "admin@local",
            "scopes": ["read", "write", "admin"]
        },
        "dev-readonly-token": {
            "client_id": "reader@local",
            "scopes": ["read"]
        }
    }
)

# Only enable in development
if os.getenv("ENV") == "development":
    mcp = FastMCP(name="Exarp", auth=verifier)
```

**Use cases:**
- Local development without auth infrastructure
- Testing scope-based access control
- Demo environments

🎯 **Objective:** Replace CLI args with portable fastmcp.json

📋 **Reference:** https://gofastmcp.com/deployment/server-configuration

**Create fastmcp.json:**
```json
{
  "$schema": "https://gofastmcp.com/public/schemas/fastmcp.json/v1.json",
  "source": {
    "path": "project_management_automation/server.py",
    "entrypoint": "mcp"
  },
  "environment": {
    "type": "uv",
    "python": ">=3.10",
    "dependencies": [
      "fastmcp",
      "pydantic",
      "networkx",
      "mcp"
    ]
  },
  "deployment": {
    "transport": "stdio",
    "log_level": "INFO",
    "env": {
      "PROJECT_ROOT": "."
    }
  }
}
```

**Benefits:**
- Simple: `fastmcp run` instead of complex CLI
- Portable: Works with Cursor, Claude Desktop, VS Code
- Declarative: Single source of truth
- IDE support: JSON schema for autocomplete

